{
  "article_id": "UticaDailyObserver1879",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The following story, related and vouched for by the San Francisco Chronicle as true in every particular, possesses a remarkable similarity in many of its incidents to the ingenious tale of fiction woven by ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "De Foe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "dde",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ":",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In the spring of 1835 the schooner "
      },
      {
        "text": "[Peor es] Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", built at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Monterey",
        "entity_key": "ci_mo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was chartered by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lewis T. Burton",
        "entity_key": "lbu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac J. Sparks",
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "for an otter-hunting expedition from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "sailed in May, but the trip not proving so successful as was anticipated, she returned as far as north as "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she remained at anchor during a portion of the month of August of the same year. It being known that the small island of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", situated about seventy miles southwest of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and a little further southeast from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the "
      },
      {
        "text": "[Peor es] Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was despatched to remove them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nineteen men, women and children",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were taken on board "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which was preparing to depart, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the Indian mothers",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "two of her offspring",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been forgotten and left on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "With true maternal devotion she sprang into the water and swam to the shore in search of ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the missing children",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of which was three years of age and the other an infant unable to walk.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Her hurried search was unavailing, and, abandoning all hope of finding "
      },
      {
        "text": "the babes",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she returned to the beach just in time to see "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "sailing away with all her friends on board. She called frantically for some one to take her to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but received no reply but the one sad word, man yana (to-morrow), which never after ceased to ring in her ears and was repeated on her dying bed."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "never went back to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which was not again visited until 1851, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", another hunter, stopped there for a few days. "
      },
      {
        "text": "He was not previously aware that the place was inhabited, but on this occasion he became convinced that such was the case. He noticed",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}